Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to trigger an automation when the Master Bedroom Lamp is physically turned on. This corresponds to a COC event with command "DFON" sent by the device.
2. The action is to turn on the Master Bedroom Lamp to 75% brightness.
3. The ramp rate should be set to "fast". Among the ramp rate enums, the fastest is 0.1 seconds (index 31).
4. The automation condition checks for the COC "DFON" command from Master Bedroom Lamp.
5. The actions are to set ramp rate to 0.1 seconds and then turn on the lamp at 75% brightness.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Fast On Ramp to 75% on Physical Turn On of Master Bedroom Lamp",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Master Bedroom Lamp",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "Master Bedroom Lamp",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Ramp Rate", "value": 31, "uom": "enum", "precision": 0 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Master Bedroom Lamp",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "Level", "value": 75, "uom": "%", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
